						<div class="postbody"><img src="./images/smilies/icon_twisted.gif" alt=":twisted:" title="Twisted Evil" /> Hello!  I'm not necesarrily a newb to NES, but I am to tinkering with electronics.  I have just bought a Japanese Power glove which uses the famicom's 15 pin expansion port.  Now, I am wondering how I could use this on my current NES.  It is a NES one.  I have been looking on google for pin-out data and such, but alas, it is all pretty much gibberish to be and such I think I may funk up my NES or power glove if I try something w/o your guys help.  If this has been partially answered in another thread or something, I do not mind If you direct me to it.  Also, I know I could get an american power glove for suprisingly cheap since they aren't in high demand, but I find the jap version to be cooler, plus not many have seen it before.  Came CIB (I believe, manual, box, styro, all connectors, but for some reason only one part of the box came, but for 20 bucks, I think I can deal) so I am very happy.  I hope someone can help, thanks in advance!</div>

